"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874893","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-17","<p>NHS England has received a Preliminary Policy Proposal for the use of Sapropterin in the management of phenylketonuria for adults and children, as it is considered by the Clinical Lead that new evidence has now been published to support its use.</p><p> </p><p>This was considered by the Specialised Services Clinical Panel where it was agreed that, as this is a licensed medicine, it should be referred to National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) for consideration through its technology appraisal process. NICE has confirmed receipt of referral and will be advising on the decision making process and timetable in due course.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-04-17T14:03:11.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874893/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874893/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874893/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-29","Sapropterin","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, when he expects NHS England and NICE to make a decision on licensing Kuvan for the treatment of phenylketonuria","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","135194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874894","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-17","<p>The Clinical Expert Group for Lung Cancer published three documents in 2017/18, and also provided clinical advice for the development of a handbook to support delivery of best practice lung cancer pathways. Details of the documents and handbook are provided below.</p><p>- National Optimal Lung Cancer Pathway (2017);</p><p>- National Optimal Lung Cancer Pathway Implementation Guide (2017);</p><p>- Clinical Advice for the Provision of Lung Cancer Services (2017); and</p><p>- Handbook: Implementing a timed lung cancer diagnostic pathway (2018).</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-04-17T13:51:05.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874894/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874894/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874894/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-29","Lung Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will set out recent advice and guidance provided by NHS England's Clinical Expert Group on the early detection and diagnosis of lung cancer.","false","Biography information for James Brokenshire","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","135195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874895","Department for Education","false","2018-04-16","<p>Legislation and funding agreements require all state funded schools to deliver Religious Education (RE). Ofsted does not routinely compliance check whether schools, Standing Advisory Councils on Religious Education (SACREs) or Agreed Syllabus Conferences (ASC) are meeting all of their statutory requirements. Where during the course of a school inspection it becomes clear that statutory requirements are not being met, and this is a contributory factor in explaining why pupils are not achieving as well as they should at the school, it will be considered for inclusion in the inspection report as a key point for improvement.</p><p> </p><p>Although Ofsted does not inspect individual curriculum subjects, it is required to report on the spiritual, moral, social and cultural development of pupils. Maintained faith schools are required to arrange a separate inspection of denominational RE and collective worship, leading to published reports.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","135192","2018-04-16T11:06:04.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874895/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874895/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874895/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-29","Standing Advisory Councils on Religious Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what discussions he and his Department have had with Ofsted since 2015 on whether Standing Advisory Councils on Religious Education and Agreed Syllabus Conferences are complying with their statutory obligations; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","135196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874896","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-16","<p>The UK will continue to work closely with other countries and stakeholders to champion the conservation and welfare of cetaceans. It is hoped this will ensure strong support for the maintenance of the global moratorium on commercial whaling, both in the build up to and after the forthcoming International Whaling Commission meeting in September.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-04-16T11:27:03.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874896/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874896/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874896/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-29","Whales: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps he is taking to ensure that the moratorium on commercial whaling is maintained after the forthcoming International Whaling Committee meeting.","false","Biography information for Stephen Morgan","Portsmouth South","Stephen Morgan","135197"
