"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873586","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-20","<p>The action taken by mobile operators as a result of the 2014 agreement with Government, has helped to improve coverage on the UK's roads. We recognise that there is further to go, which is why the Government has a Manifesto commitment to deliver full and uninterrupted mobile phone signal on all major roads by 2022.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","134701","2018-04-20T11:47:28.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873586/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873586/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873586/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-28","Mobile Phones: Motorways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what his Department's timescale is for eliminating mobile phone not-spots on motorways.","false","Biography information for Luke Graham","Ochil and South Perthshire","Luke Graham","134700"
