"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873606","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-17","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, has regular discussions with Cabinet colleagues on improving the health and wellbeing of children.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-04-17T15:32:07.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873606/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873606/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873606/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-28","Children: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what discussions he has had with his Cabinet colleagues on measures to protect children from junk food marketing.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","134720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873607","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-17","<p>The franchise agreement between the Government and each individual TOC includes benchmarks in three key areas – punctuality, cancellations and capacity. The Department monitors each train operator’s overall performance against these areas regularly and there are clear actions set out in the franchise agreement should performance drop below what is expected.</p><p> </p><p>Further details can be find in the franchise agreement under Schedule 7.1, which can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/london-and-south-eastern-railway-limited" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/london-and-south-eastern-railway-limited</a></p><p> </p><p>In terms of the future franchise, the Department set out its expectations in the Invitation To Tender which can be found at</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/664302/south-eastern-franchise-itt.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/664302/south-eastern-franchise-itt.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-04-17T10:27:23.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873607/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873607/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873607/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-03-28","South Eastern Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what targets his Department sets to measure the performance of the Southeastern rail franchise.","false","Biography information for Tom Tugendhat","Tonbridge and Malling","Tom Tugendhat","134721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873608","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-18","<p>As well as regular formal meetings with trusts, NHS Improvement has multiple day-to-day interactions with them which include discussions around financial performance.</p><p> </p><p>The frequency of these meetings will depend on the nature and extent of the challenges the trusts face. For example where a trust is not meeting its control total, or is at risk of not meeting it, NHS Improvement will have regular and frequent contact to ensure that the trust is doing everything it can to deliver improvements.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-04-18T12:39:25.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873608/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873608/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/873608/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-28","NHS Improvement: NHS Trusts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many meetings have taken place between NHS Improvement and NHS trusts to agree plans to improve their financial position since 2010; which providers have had such meetings with NHS Improvement; and when each such meeting took place.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","134722"
